"7801","Internet Gambling (U.S. Region Only)","Merchants licensed in accordance with applicable law or regulation\\nto operate an Internet gambling system or platform accepting the\\nplacement of wagers.\\nUse of this MCC is restricted to merchants located in the U.S. region\\nand properly registered with Mastercard as set forth in section 9.4.2\\nof the Security Rules and Procedures manual.","Amusement and Entertainment","CCR1 CR05 GAM2 U001","COLM"
"7802","Government Licensed Horse/Dog Racing (U.S. Region Only)","Merchants licensed in accordance with applicable law or regulation\\nto conduct horse or dog racing or pari-mutuel wagering activities in\\nconnection therewith, or both.\\nUse of this MCC is restricted to merchants located in the U.S. region\\nand properly registered with Mastercard as set forth in section 9.4.2\\nof the Security Rules and Procedures manual.","Amusement and Entertainment","CCR1 CR05 GAM2 U001","COLM"
"7829","Motion Picture and Video Tape Production and Distribution","Wholesale producers and distributors of educational and industrial\\nfilms and videos for exhibition and sale, including TV commercials\\nand training films.\\nFor retailers that rent videotapes to consumers, use MCC 7841.","Wholesale Distributors and Manufacturers","CCR3 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHNA COLM JA02 JPNG OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 TT01-TTO UR10"
"7832","Motion Picture Theaters","Merchants that operate movie theaters, including drive-in theaters.\\nSuch merchants sell tickets and refreshments, and may or may not\\noffer advance ticket reservations via the phone.","Amusement and Entertainment","CCR1 CNV1 CNV2 CR03 EM04 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32 ST01","BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLE CHLM CHN8 CHNA COL7 EM03 JA02 JPNF OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PR06 QPS1 S003 TT01-TTO UR10"
"7841","Video Entertainment Rental Stores","Merchants that rent videotapes, laser discs, DVDs, and video games\\nfor consumer use at home. Such merchants may or may not sell a\\nlimited selection of used videos, drinks, candy, snacks, and blank\\ntapes.","Amusement and Entertainment","CR1 CR03 EM04 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32 ST01 ST02","BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHLM CHN8 CHNA COLN JA02 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA01 QPS1 TT01-TTO UR10"
"7911","Dance Halls, Schools, and Studios","Merchants that operate dance studios, dance schools, and public\\ndance halls or ballrooms, and charge for admission fees, lessons, and\\nrefreshments. Such merchants may teach many types of dance or\\nspecialize in tap and ballet, ballroom, square dance instruction, or\\nother types of dance.","Amusement and Entertainment","CCR1 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHNA JA02 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 TT01-TTO UR10"
"7922","Theatrical Producers (except Motion Pictures), Ticket Agencies","Merchants that operate live theatrical productions, such as road\\ncompanies and summer theater groups. Services associated with\\ntheatrical productions and concerts are also included, such as casting\\nagencies, booking agencies, scenery, lighting, and other equipment\\nservices, and theatrical ticket agencies.\\nFor movie theaters, use MCC 7832.","Amusement and Entertainment","CCR1 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHNA COL& JA02 JPNF OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 TT01-TTO UR10"
"7929","Bands, Orchestras, and Miscellaneous Entertainers: not elsewhere classified","Merchants that provide entertainment other than theatrical\\nproductions, and includes musicians, bands, orchestras, comedians,\\nand magicians. Merchants that specialize in providing music (live\\nbands or disc jockeys [DJs]) for weddings or special events are also\\nincluded.","Amusement and Entertainment","CCR1 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHNA COLN JA02 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 TT01-TTO UR10"
"7932","Pool and Billiard Establishments","Merchants operating establishments that rent pool or billiard tables\\nfor entertainment. Such merchants may offer coin-operated pool\\ntables, or may rent pool tables by the game or by the hour.\\nShuffleboard, darts, and other games and refreshments may also be\\navailable.","Amusement and Entertainment","CCR1 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHNA JA02 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 TT01-TTO UR10"
"7933","Bowling Alleys","Merchants that operate bowling alleys for entertainment, and may\\naccept Mastercard cards for rental fees, pro shop purchases,\\nrefreshments, or usage fees.\\nMerchants located within the bowling alley that are separately\\nmanaged must be classified with the appropriate MCC for that type\\nof business.\\nFor example, a restaurant located within a bowling alley must use\\nMCC 5812; a bar must use MCC 5813.","Amusement and Entertainment","CCR1 CR03 EM04 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHNA COLN JA02 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 TT01-TTO UR10"
"7941","Athletic Fields, Commercial Sports, Professional Sports Clubs, Sports","Merchants that operate and promote semiprofessional and\\nprofessional athletic clubs (such as baseball, basketball, football,\\nhockey, and soccer), promote amateur and professional athletic\\nevents, and manage individual athletes. Sports arenas and stadiums\\nare also included.","Amusement and Entertainment","CCR1 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHNA COLN JA02 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 SPN3 TT01-TTO UR10"
"7991","Tourist Attractions and Exhibits","Merchants that operate tourist attractions and exhibits for\\nentertainment, such as expositions, botanical gardens, craft shows,\\nmuseums, and wineries.\\nFor art exhibits held at art galleries, use MCC 5971.","Amusement and Entertainment","CCR1 CR03 GW01 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHNA COLN JA02 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 TT01-TTO UR10"
"7992","Golf Courses, Public","Merchants that operate public golf courses. Services offered may\\ninclude greens fees and golf cart or equipment rentals.\\nFor restaurants and cafes located at the golf course, use MCC 5812.\\nFor pro shops that sell golfing supplies and equipment, use MCC\\n5941.\\nFor country clubs and private golf courses, use MCC 7997.","Amusement and Entertainment","CCR1 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHNA COLN JA02 JPNF OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 TT01-TTO UR10"
"7993","Video Amusement Game Supplies","Merchants that sell coin-operated amusement machines, equipment,\\nand supplies. Products for sale may include video game machines,\\njuke boxes, pinball machines, slot machines, mechanical games, and\\ninstant photograph booths.\\nFor merchants that operate video and game arcades, use MCC\\n7994.","Amusement and Entertainment","CCR1 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHNA COLN JA02 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 TT01-TTO UR10"
"7994","Video Game Arcades/Establishments","Merchants that operate indoor playgrounds, interactive games and\\namusement machines, such as jukeboxes, video games, pinball\\nmachines, paintball, and laser tag games, mechanical games, and\\ninstant photograph booths.\\nAn acquirer may use this MCC to identify a U.S. region skill games\\nmerchant or a skill games merchant located outside the U.S. region\\nthat accepts payment from U.S. region cardholders for participation\\nin a skill game conducted by such merchant. Such merchant must be\\nproperly registered with Mastercard as set forth in section 9.4.5 of\\nthe Security Rules and Procedures manual. If such merchant's\\nactivities are regulated as gambling in any non-U.S. jurisdiction, then\\nthe merchant must be identified with MCC 7995.\\nFor merchants that sell amusement equipment, use MCC 7993.\\nFor merchants that operate games involving wagering, use MCC\\n7995.","Amusement and Entertainment","CCR1 CR03 EM04 GAM2 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHNA COLN JA02 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 SPN3 TT01-TTO UR10"
"7995","Gambling Transactions","Any transaction, other than an ATM transaction, involving the placing\\nof a wager, the purchase of a lottery ticket, spread betting, in-flight\\ncommerce gaming, or the purchase of chips or other value usable for\\ngambling in conjunction with gambling activities provided by\\nwagering or betting establishments such as casinos, race tracks, card\\nparlors, airlines, and the like.\\nGambling transaction processing requirements are set forth in\\nsection 5.1.2.2 of the Mastercard Rules manual.\\nAny fee charged and included in the total transaction amount must\\nbe clearly disclosed to the cardholder before completing the\\ntransaction. Such a fee must not be charged for in-flight commerce\\ngaming transactions.\\nBefore acquiring transactions reflecting non-face-to-face gambling,\\nan acquirer must first register the merchant with Mastercard as\\ndescribed in section 9.2 of the Security Rules and Procedures manual.\\nFor other types of purchases associated with the establishment,\\nsuch as food, lodging, or passage, use the MCC that best describes\\nthat transaction.\\nFor information about Gaming Payment Transactions, refer to\\nChapter 6 in the Transaction Processing Rules manual.","Amusement and Entertainment","CCR1 CR05 U001","BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLE CHLM COLM GAM1 JA02 SPN4 TT01-TTO U003"
"7996","Amusement Parks, Carnivals, Circuses, Fortune Tellers","Merchants that operate amusement parks and carnivals offering\\nmechanical rides, snacks and food stands, games, animal exhibits,\\nand entertainment. Circuses, fortune tellers, astrologers, tarot card\\nreaders, and mystics also are included.","Amusement and Entertainment","CCR1 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR03 BR08 CHLG CHLM CHNA COLN JA02 JPNF OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 TT01-TTO UR10"
"7997","Clubs: Country Clubs, Membership (Athletic, Recreation, Sports), Private Golf","Merchants that operate sports and recreation facilities requiring\\nmembership. Examples of such facilities include exercise, athletic,\\nand health clubs, country clubs, private golf courses, boating yacht\\nclubs, swimming clubs, tennis clubs, bowling leagues, riding clubs,\\nshooting and gun clubs, and racquetball clubs. Such merchants may\\nor may not provide massage services and spa services such as facials,\\nweight control counseling, aromatherapy, steam baths, and\\nwhirlpools.\\nFor merchants that primarily provide massages, use MCC 7297.\\nFor merchants that primarily operate a spa and its related services,\\nuse MCC 7298.","Amusement and Entertainment","CCR1 CR03 GW01 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR01 CHLE CHNA COLA HK02 JA02 JPNF MAC2 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 SPN3 TT01-TTO UR10"
"7998","Aquariums, Dolphinariums, Zoos, and Seaquariums","Merchants that operate sea life parks and zoos for the\\nentertainment and education of the general public.\\nOther services located on the premises, such as restaurants or gift\\nshops, must be classified with the MCC that best describes that type\\nof business.","Amusement and Entertainment","CCR1 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR03 BR08 CHLG CHNA COLN JA02 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 TT01-TTO UR10"
"7999","Recreation Services: not elsewhere classified","Merchants that provide a wide variety of recreation and\\nentertainment services that are not described by another, more\\nspecific MCC. Typically, these merchants provide services that require\\nactive physical participation such as swimming, playing miniature\\ngolf, snow skiing, miniature car racing, ice skating, rock climbing,\\nskate boarding and horseback riding. These merchants may also rent\\nbicycles, aircraft, motorcycles, go-carts, and other sporting\\nequipment. As a general rule, these merchants are not clubs and do\\nnot require membership.\\nFor private sports and recreation clubs requiring membership, use\\nMCC 7997.\\nFor boat rentals, use MCC 4457.\\nFor public golf courses, use MCC 7992.","Amusement and Entertainment","CCR1 CR03 GW01 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLE CHLM CHNA COLN JA02 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 SPN3 TT01-TTO UR10"
"8011","Doctors: not elsewhere classified","Licensed physicians engaged in a practice of general or specialized\\nmedicine and surgery that is not more accurately identified by\\nanother more specific MCC. Such merchants include plastic and\\ncosmetic surgeons, dermatologists, psychiatrists, radiologists,\\northopedists, pediatricians, neurologists, obstetricians, and\\ngynecologists.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR04 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLH CHNA COLJ JA02 JPN1 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 PR06 TT01-TTO UR09"
"8021","Dentists, Orthodontists","Licensed physicians that practice general or specialized dentistry,\\nsuch as dental surgery.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR04 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLH CHNA COLJ JA02 JPN1 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 PR06 TT01-TTO UR09"
"8031","Osteopathic Physicians","Licensed physicians that provide therapy involving the non-surgical\\nmanipulation and adjustment of bone structures.\\nFor orthopedists that provide surgical treatments, use MCC 8011.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR04 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHNA COLJ JA02 JPN1 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 PR06 TT01-TTO UR09"
"8041","Chiropractors","Medical professionals that provide therapy in which the spinal\\ncolumn and limbs are manipulated and adjusted.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR04 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHNA COLJ JA02 JPN1 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 PR06 TT01-TTO UR09"
"8042","Optometrists, Ophthalmologists","Optometrists are medical professionals that examine and treat eye\\ndefects with corrective lenses or exercises. Ophthalmologists are\\nlicensed physicians that specialize in the structures, functions, and\\ndiseases of the eye, and may perform surgery. These merchants may\\nor may not fill eyeglass or contact lens prescriptions, or sell eyeglass\\nframes.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR04 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHNA COLJ JA02 JPN1 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 PR06 TT01-TTO UR09"
"8043","Opticians, Optical Goods, and Eyeglasses","Merchants that read prescriptions for visual correction, order lenses,\\nmake and sell eyeglasses and contact lenses, and may perform eye\\nexaminations. Opticians may also sell a variety of optical goods such\\nas safety glasses, sunglasses (prescription and regular), carrying\\ncases, and eyeglass and contact lens solutions. One-hour eyeglasses\\nmerchants generally located in shopping malls are included.\\nFor merchants that examine eyes and treat eye defects with\\nprocedures that may involve surgery or surgical techniques, use MCC\\n8042.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR04 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLH CHNA COLJ JA02 JPN1 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 PR06 TT01-TTO UR09"
"8049","Chiropodists, Podiatrists","Licensed physicians specializing in the diagnosis and treatment of\\nfoot ailments.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR04 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLH CHNA COLJ JA02 JPN1 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 PR06 TT01-TTO UR09"
"8050","Nursing and Personal Care Facilities","Merchants that provide inpatient nursing and health-related\\npersonal care services. Because of their mental or physical condition,\\npatients in these facilities may require the administration of\\nmedications and treatments or the supervision of self-administered\\nmedications in accordance with a physician’s orders. This MCC\\nincludes convalescent homes, nursing homes, hospice facilities, and\\neldercare facilities that provide long-term care and generally do not\\nperform surgery.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR04 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLH CHNA COLJ JA02 JPN1 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 PR06 TT01-TTO UR09"
"8062","Hospitals","Hospitals that provide diagnostic services, extensive medical\\ntreatment including surgery, and other hospital services, as well as\\ncontinuous nursing services for the sick and injured. Includes mental\\nand psychiatric hospitals, children’s hospitals, and maternity\\nhospitals.\\nFor pet clinics or pet hospitals, use MCC 0742.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR04 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLH CHNA COLJ JA02 JPN1 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 PR06 SPN3 TT01-TTO UR09"
"8071","Dental and Medical Laboratories","Merchants that provide services to medical and dental professionals\\nand to patients referred by physicians or dentists. Includes medical\\nlaboratories that perform biological analysis, blood analysis,\\nurinalysis, X-ray, bacteriological analysis, and diagnostic analysis, and\\ndental laboratories that make dentures, artificial teeth, crowns and\\nbridges, and customized orthodontic appliances.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR04 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLH CHNA COLJ JA02 JPN1 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 PR06 TT01-TTO UR09"
"8099","Health Practitioners, Medical Services: not elsewhere classified","Medical professionals that are not described by another, more\\nspecific MCC. Examples include physical therapists, occupational\\ntherapists, psychologists, and other health practitioners such as\\nblood banks, planned parenthood clinics, fertility clinics, chemical\\ndependency centers, hearing testing services, licensed massage\\ntherapists, surgical hair replacement clinics, and sports medicine\\nclinics.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR04 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLF CHNA COLJ JA02 JPN1 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 PR06 TT01-TTO UR09"
"8111","Attorneys, Legal Services","Merchants that are operated by members of the bar and provide\\nlegal advice and services. Such merchants may specialize in one area\\nof litigation such as divorce or bankruptcy, or provide a full spectrum\\nof legal services.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHNA COLL JA02 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PR06 TT01-TTO UR09"
"8211","Schools, Elementary and Secondary","Elementary and secondary schools that provide academic instruction\\nfrom kindergarten through twelfth grade, including public, private,\\nparochial, and boarding schools.\\nFor preschools, use MCC 8351.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR2 CR03 EDU1 EM01 EM02 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 AUS2 BR01 CHL5 CHNA COLH EM05 JA02 JPN8 MAC2 NZE1 OTH8 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 PR06 UR09"
"8220","Colleges, Universities, Professional Schools, and Junior Colleges","Community and junior colleges, universities, theological seminaries,\\nand professional schools (including dental, law, engineering, and\\nmedical) that provide academic courses and grant academic\\ndegrees. The requirement for admission must be at least a high\\nschool diploma or its equivalent.\\nFor business and secretarial schools, use MCC 8244.\\nFor vocational and trade schools, use MCC 8249.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR2 CR03 COLH EDU1 EM01 EM02 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 AUS2 BR01 CHL5 CHNA EM05 JA02 JPN8 MAC2 NZE1 OTH8 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 PR06 SPN3 UR09"
"8241","Schools, Correspondence","Correspondence schools that offer educational instruction through\\nthe mail by sending lessons and examinations to the student.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR2 CR03 EDU1 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 AUS2 BR01 CHLG CHNA COLH JA02 JPN8 MAC2 NZE1 OTH8 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 PR06 UR09"
"8244","Schools, Business and Secretarial","Business and secretarial schools that offer general business training\\nsuch as business machine operation, office procedures, word\\nprocessing, stenographic, and other clerical skills. Such schools offer\\na training certificate but do not offer academic degrees.\\nFor vocational and trade schools, use MCC 8249.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR2 CR03 EDU1 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 AUS2 BR01 CHLG CHNA COLH JA02 JPN8 MAC2 NZE1 OTH8 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 PR06 SPN3 UR09"
"8249","Schools, Trade and Vocational","Trade and vocational schools that offer training and instruction in\\nspecialized professions such as welding, mechanics, carpentry, real\\nestate, and truck driving. Such schools offer a training certificate but\\ndo not offer academic degrees.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR2 CR03 EDU1 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 AUS2 BR01 CHLG CHNA COLH JA02 JPN8 MAC2 NZE1 OTH8 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 PR06 UR09"
"8299","Schools and Educational Services: not elsewhere classified","Merchants that offer educational courses and services that are not\\ndescribed by another more specific MCC. Such merchants include\\nschools that teach music, drama, art, cooking, modeling, karate\\nschools, automobile driving instruction, traffic safety, flying\\ninstruction, and sewing or knitting instruction.\\nFor dance schools, use MCC 7911.\\nFor schools that grant academic degrees for courses of study in\\nmusic, drama, and art, uses MCC 8220.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR2 CR03 EDU1 EM01 EM02 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 AUS2 BR01 CHL5 CHNA COLH EM05 JA02 JPN8 MAC2 NZE1 OTH8 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 PR06 UR09"
"8351","Child Care Services","Merchants that provide child care services, including nannies, nursery\\nschools, and day care centers. These merchants typically care for\\ninfants and preschool children, but may also care for older children,\\nand may or may not provide educational programs.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR03 EDU1 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","ARG2 AUS2 BR01 CHL5 CHNA COLH EM05 JA02 JPN8 NZE1 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PA02 PR06 UR09"
"8398","Organizations, Charitable and Social Service","Charitable (non-political) organizations that solicit contributions,\\nsocial service organizations that provide social welfare services,\\nadvocacy groups, community organizations, and health agencies.\\nUse a TCC of T for fundraising performed through non–face-to-face\\nmethods such as phone orders.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CH01 CCR3 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH5","BEL1 BR01 CAN5 CAN6 CH02 CHL2 CHNA CHRT CM01 JA01 JPN1 PR05 TT01-TTO"
"8641","Associations: Civic, Social, and Fraternal","Associations engaged in civic, social, or fraternal activities. Such\\nassociations include alumni associations and clubs, booster clubs,\\nbusinesspersons clubs, community membership clubs, fraternal\\nlodges, fraternities and sororities, social clubs, veterans’\\norganizations, and youth associations.\\nThe activities of these groups may include political fund-raising;\\nhowever, if this is the primary purpose of the organization, use MCC\\n8651.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR01 CHLG CHNA COLM HK02 JA02 MAC2 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PR06 TT01-TTO UR09"
"8651","Organizations, Political","Membership organizations that promote the interests of a national,\\nstate, or local political party or candidate, including political groups\\norganized specifically to raise funds for a political party or individual\\ncandidate.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHNA COLM JA02 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PR06 TT01-TTO UR10"
"8661","Organizations, Religious","Religious organizations that provide worship services, religious\\ntraining or study, religious activities, and fund-raising. Examples are\\nchurches, convents, monasteries, mosques, shrines, synagogues, and\\ntemples.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR01 CH02 CHLG CHNA COLM JA02 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PR05 PR06 TT01-TTO"
"8675","Automobile Associations","Automobile associations and clubs. Such merchants provide\\nmembers with special services such as travel and road condition\\ninformation, maps and guides, and specials rates at restaurants,\\nhotels, and car rental agencies. These merchants often charge an\\nannual membership fee.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR01 CHLG CHNA COLM HK02 JA02 JPNF MAC2 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PR06 TT01-TTO UR10"
"8699","Organizations, Membership: not elsewhere classified","Organizations or associations that are not described by another,\\nmore specific MCC. Examples include historical clubs, labor unions,\\npoetry clubs, art councils, and tenant or condominium associations.\\nFor membership to health and athletic clubs, use MCC 7997.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR01 CHLG CHNA COLM HK02 JA02 MAC2 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PR06 TT01-TTO UR10"
"8734","Testing Laboratories (Non–Medical)","Merchants that provide non-medical testing services to other\\nbusinesses. Examples of such services include automobile testing,\\ncalibration, and certification, food testing, forensic testing, product\\nand pollution testing, and industrial X-ray inspection services.\\nFor medical testing laboratories, use MCC 8071.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHNA COLM JA02 JPNG OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PR06 UR10"
"8911","Architectural, Engineering, and Surveying Services","Merchants that provide professional architectural, engineering, and\\nland, water, and aerial surveying services. Included are home and\\nbuilding designers, ship, boat, and machine engineers and designers,\\nand architectural engineers.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLB CHLK CHNA COLL JA02 OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PR06 SPN3 TT01-TTO UR10"
"8931","Accounting, Auditing, and Bookkeeping Services","Merchants that provide accounting, bookkeeping, billing, payroll and\\nother related auditing services, including Certified Public\\nAccountants (CPAs). Such merchants also may provide income tax\\npreparation services in addition to accounting and auditing services.\\nFor merchants that provide income tax preparation services without\\nalso providing accounting, auditing, and bookkeeping services, use\\nMCC 7276.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLG CHNA COLL JA02 JPNG OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PR06 TT01-TTO UR10"
"8999","Professional Services: not elsewhere classified","Merchants engaged in traditional professions that offer highly\\nspecialized services, and often require employees to obtain advanced\\nor specialized education or training to provide the services. This MCC\\nshould be used only if the merchant’s business is not described by\\nanother, more specific MCC. Examples of such merchants include\\nmortgage brokers, research firms, financial planners, graphic\\ndesigners, guest speakers and lecturers, court stenographers, real\\nestate appraisers, research firms, and auction houses.","Professional Services and Membership Organizations","CCR3 CR03 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32","BEL1 BR07 BR10 CHLE CHNA COLL JA02 JPNG OTH8 OT33 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PR06 SPN3 TT01-TTO UR10"
"9211","Court Costs including Alimony and Child Support","Local, state, and federal courts of law that administer and process\\ncourt fees (such as case administration costs and litigation\\nprocessing fees), alimony, and child support payments.\\nFor merchants that process fines or penalties associated with the\\ncourt system, use MCC 9222.","Government Services","CCR3 CR03 EM01 EM02 GVT1 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32 PS01","ARG1 AUS1 BR02 CHLG CHNA COLM EM03 JA02 NZG1 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PR02 PS02 UR10"
"9222","Fines","Government entities that administer and process local, state, and\\nfederal fines and penalties, motor vehicle violations, and community\\nor property assessed fines.","Government Services","CCR3 CR03 EM01 EM02 GVT1 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32 PS01","ARG1 AUS1 BR02 CHLG CHNA COLM EM03 JA01 NZG1 OTH8 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PR02 PS02 UR10"
"9223","Bail and Bond Payments","Merchants that post bail to the court system as security for the\\nappearance of the arraigned individual.","Government Services","CCR3 CR03 EM01 EM02 GVT1 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32 PS01","ARG1 AUS1 BR02 CHLG CHNA COLM EM03 JA02 NZG1 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PR02 UR10"
"9311","Tax Payments","Local, state, and federal entities that engage in financial\\nadministration and taxation, including the collection of taxes and\\npenalties and the custody and disbursement of funds. Such\\nmerchants include property tax assessors’ offices, customs bureaus,\\nand state tax commissions.","Government Services","CCR3 CF01 CR03 EM01 EM02 GVT1 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32 PS01","ARG1 AUS1 BR02 CHL1 CHNA COL3 EM03 EM05 JA01 NZG1 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PR02 UR09"
"9399","Government Services: not elsewhere classified","Merchants that provide general support services to the government\\nsuch as personnel, auditing, procurement, and building management\\nservices, and are not described by another, more specific MCC.\\nExamples include civil rights and civil service commissions, general\\ngovernment accounting offices, general services offices, government\\nsupply agencies, police, fire, and motor vehicle departments, and\\nnational, state, and city parks.\\nFor intra-government transfers (IGOTS) program transactions, use\\nMCC 9405.\\nFor state universities and colleges, use MCC 8220.\\nMerchants involved in the sale of goods or services to the\\ngovernment should use the wholesale MCC that best describes the\\nbusiness.","Government Services","CCR3 CF01 CR03 EM01 EM02 GVT1 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32 PS01","ARG1 AUS1 BR02 CHLA CHN8 CHN9 CHNA COLD EM03 JA01 JPN1 NZG1 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 PR02 PS02 SPN3 UR09 UR09"
"9402","Postal Services: Government Only","Government postal offices, including local post office branches.\\nServices provided include accepting and processing packages and\\nmail for delivery, selling postage stamps, and express mailing\\nservices.\\nFor mail packaging stores that provide packaging services and sell\\nstamps, greeting cards, and wrapping, and that may also provide\\nservices for UPS, Federal Express, and other express mail services,\\nuse MCC 7399.","Government Services","CCR3 CF01 CR03 EM01 EM02 OTH1 OTH2 OTH3 OTH4 OTH5 OTH6 OT11 OT12 OT13 OT14 OT15 OT16 OT21 OT22 OT25 OT32 PS01 ST01","AUS1 BEL1 BR02 CHLG CHNA COLM EM03 JA01 JPN1 NZG1 OT34 OT36 OT39 OT40 OT41 TT01-TTO UR09"
